When running opencode with attached files, use this syntax:

  opencode run "your message here" -f file1.md -f file2.md

The message must come FIRST, before -f flags. If you put the message after -f, opencode treats it as another file path and fails with "File not found."

Example:
  cd /workspace/my-project
  opencode run "Build the app described in prompt.md" -f prompt.md
